SimpleAllele.Comment: NCBI staff provided an HGVS expression for allelic variant 614144.0002 from the boundaries of the genes reported to be deleted in Supplementary Table 1 of the paper by Hopp et al., 2011 (PubMed 21493627).

AttributeSet.Attribute: Meckel syndrome is a severe autosomal recessive ciliopathy classically defined by the triad of encephalocele, polydactyly, and renal and biliary ductal dysplasia (summary by Hopp et al., 2011). For a general phenotypic description and a discussion of genetic heterogeneity of Meckel syndrome, see MKS1 (249000).

ObservedData.Attribute: For discussion of the 1.71-Mb deletion in the B9D1 gene that was found in compound heterozygous state in a patient with Meckel syndrome type 9 (MKS9; 614209) by Hopp et al. (2011), see 614144.0001.
